video.title: Liv and Maddie
video.synopsis: After four years in Hollywood as a television star, Liv returns to Wisconsin to discover that either she -- or her family -- has changed.

episodes.synopsis: Liv's plan to find Maddie a date for the school dance backfires, angering her twin. Meanwhile, Joey and Parker's antics annoy Liv.
episodes.title: Twin-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: As the new captain of the basketball team, Maddie protests when the principal cuts their budget, but the rest of the team doesn't have her back.
episodes.title: Team-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv wants to bond with her younger brother, Parker, so she volunteers to host his sleepover party -- but has no idea what she's getting into.
episodes.title: Sleep-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Maddie's been busy with the basketball team, and Liv decides she needs to make other friends -- but her new pal isn't the best influence.
episodes.title: Steal-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: At the Halloween dance, Maddie tries to help Joey get over his fear of talking to girls, but things don't go quite as planned.
episodes.title: Kang-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv is supposed to judge a skateboarding competition that her boyfriend is skating in, but when he breaks up with her, she wants to back out.
episodes.title: Skate-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: While doing community service at a senior center, Liv and Maddie butt heads -- and decide to settle their differences with a game of dodgeball.
episodes.title: Dodge-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv wants to prove that she's smart, so she persuades Joey to let her join his Brain Olympics team, but he won't listen to her ideas.
episodes.title: Brain-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: To celebrate their Sweet 16, Liv plans a surprise party for Maddie. But a misunderstanding threatens to spoil the fun.
episodes.title: Sweet 16-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv is invited to sing at the town's annual holiday spectacular, but her young duet partner tries to steal the spotlight.
episodes.title: Fa-La-La A Rooney

episodes.synopsis: After Maddie fails her driver's test, Liv offers to switch places with her and give it a try -- but they forget about one very important detail.
episodes.title: Switch-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Maddie and Pete partner up for a two-on-two basketball tournament, but Maddie ditches him for Joey's personal trainer to get a better shot at winning.
episodes.title: Dump-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: When the house is invaded by beetles, the family needs to leave town -- but a misunderstanding makes the kids think they're moving permanently.
episodes.title: Move-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Willow's crush on Joey is making it hard for her to focus on softball tryouts. Meanwhile, Liv gets into a sticky situation before a TV appearance.
episodes.title: Slump-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv is jealous of Maddie and Karen's mother-daughter weekend plans, so she invites her TV show mom, Bree, to crash their outing.
episodes.title: Moms-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv's plans to help her twin express her girly side work a little too well when Maddie becomes obsessed with a pair of high heels.
episodes.title: Shoe-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv tries to get into character when she's up for a role as a werewolf. Meanwhile, Diggie wants to take break-dancing lessons with Maddie.
episodes.title: Howl-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Maddie is hoping she'll get the chance to try out for the Junior Olympics basketball team, but Liv is afraid of Maddie leaving her.
episodes.title: Flashback-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: When Liv's best friend visits, Maddie thinks Diggie is flirting with her. Meanwhile, Karen feels insecure when she meets Pete's ex-girlfriend.
episodes.title: BFF-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv's music video becomes a big hit -- but not because of her talent. Meanwhile, Diggie hires Maddie to work at the yogurt shop.
episodes.title: Song-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv begins shooting "Space Werewolves," and she wants to do her own stunts to prove she's a great actress -- but she's totally freaked out.
episodes.title: Space-Werewolf-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: One disaster follows another when the premiere of "Space Werewolves" clashes with the annual Stevens Point Cheddar-Brat Fest.
episodes.title: Premiere-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Maddie tries to find a hobby to pass the time as she recovers from knee surgery, Parker builds a robot dog, and Karen asks Liv for fashion tips.
episodes.title: Pottery-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: On Halloween, Maddie inadvertently casts a spell that causes Helga, Liv and Maddie's mischievous triplet to materialize.
episodes.title: Helgaween-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv befriends Korean pop star Kathy Kan, but their love of pranks may hurt Karen's chances for becoming the new vice principal.
episodes.title: Kathy Kan-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv tries to make Joey fall for Willow at a Sadie Hawkins dance, and Maddie substitute teaches at Parker's martial arts class.
episodes.title: Match-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: When Liv lands the lead role in a basketball movie, Maddie and Willow must turn her from awkward to athletic before the cameras roll.
episodes.title: Hoops-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: On New Year's Eve, Maddie is saddened that Diggie's not there to share the holiday with her, while Joey and Parker race to finish a to-do list.
episodes.title: New Year's Eve-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Joey and Parker win a bet with Liv and Maddie, who get stuck cleaning up the boys' room. During the work, Maddie gets eaten by one of Parker's chairs.
episodes.title: Bro-Cave-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv makes Maddie feel terrible after finding her twin charm bracelet in the school lost and found; Joey tries to be the perfect brother for Parker.
episodes.title: Upcycle-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv and Maddie take on guys at school who've been ranking girls based on their looks. Meanwhile, a fight prompts Joey and Parker to divide their room.
episodes.title: Rate-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Parker purposely gets detention to avoid a mother-son event. Meanwhile, Liv and Maddie make Pete's life miserable when they get sick at the same time.
episodes.title: Detention-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv makes a sequel to a muffler commercial she filmed when she was 6, and Maddie worries that her knee will affect her return to basketball.
episodes.title: Muffler-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Diggie and Maddie try to reconnect online, but Liv interferes. Meanwhile, Parker and Reggie's new face cream makes Karen grow unwanted hair.
episodes.title: Gift-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv and Karen steal a neighbor's giraffe statue, unaware of its sentimental value. Meanwhile, Parker and Maddie think they've found dinosaur bones.
episodes.title: Neighbors-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: An unfinished project from sixth grade may force Liv to take summer school, and Maddie teaches Joey how to act like a jock to impress a girl.
episodes.title: Repeat-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Maddie goes head-to-head with top class chef Artie in home economics class, and Joey gets Pete to sponsor several school clubs.
episodes.title: Cook-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Andie asks Holden to the prom just as Liv realizes she has a crush on him. Meanwhile, Karen finds a date for Maddie in Diggie's absence.
episodes.title: Prom-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Diggie and Maddie have a hard time reconnecting when he returns from Tundrabania, but Joey loves the Tundrabanian sport of flugelball.
episodes.title: Flugelball-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv puts a group together for an upcoming battle of the bands. Joey and Artie's band, on the other hand, can't seem to agree on anything.
episodes.title: Band-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Liv's new band is ready to make a video, but with disagreement over the theme, and Parker and Diggie's backstage drama, it may not get off the ground.
episodes.title: Video-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: A romantic moment passes between Liv and Holden during rehearsal. Reggie, tired of Parker calling the shots, plays basketball with Maddie.
episodes.title: Triangle-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: The principal suspects the Rooneys when Ridgewood High's new mascot is vandalized, and Maddie refuses to say where she was when it happened.
episodes.title: Frame-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: Diggie wants to tell Maddie how he feels about her before leaving for Australia. Meanwhile, Parker's favorite show ends in a cliffhanger.
episodes.title: Champ-A-Rooney

episodes.synopsis: When Maddie and Diggie attend SPARF (Stevens Point Awesome Rock Festival) with different people, they try to outdo one another's good time.
episodes.title: SPARF-A-Rooney
